Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.17,0:00:03.57,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}Following Inspector Ootaki whose behavior was suspicious,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.57,0:00:08.38,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}we ended up going to a western-style building deep in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.55,0:00:13.70,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}There, we met with siblings who were restless over an inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.32,0:00:20.41,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}Then as it was decided to take a family picture without the\Nhead of the household whose whereabouts were unknown...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.41,0:00:25.00,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}The master, who shouldn't have been there,\Nappeared in the picture in a weird state.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.52,0:00:29.96,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}After that, as everyone gathered in the dining room due\Nto being called out by a text message from the master...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.96,0:00:35.28,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}we witnessed the sinister sight of the master levitated\Nby the window and a monster flying in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.28,0:00:39.60,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}And then, we found the second son dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.81,0:00:43.46,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}Moreover, the body of the eldest daughter\Nwas found in the mid of the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.46,0:00:49.23,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}And the siblings left behind decided to wait\Nuntil dawn in their separate rooms, yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.54,0:00:52.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is unmistakably {\i1}that{\i0} person!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.11,0:00:53.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you agree, Kudou?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.49,0:00:54.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.78,0:00:56.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we have no evidence at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.91,0:01:00.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}How in the world did that person slip through the gate...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.56,0:01:02.98,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and kill Kamiyo{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} in the mid of the forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.32,0:01:10.17,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Seeking comprehensive answers, he clears all mysteries and codes!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.17,0:01:12.22,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The keen perceptive reasoning of the two...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.22,0:01:14.22,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}illuminates the darkness of the Dracula case!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.22,0:01:15.68,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.68,0:01:17.62,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Looks like a child but has the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.62,0:01:20.46,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.47,0:03:11.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, my bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.48,0:03:17.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd make Ruri drink sake to calm\Ndown, but seems like she fell asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.36,0:03:18.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So just take it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.88,0:03:20.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.55,0:03:23.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My apologies. And to think I made you bring it all the way here...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.79,0:03:25.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.33,0:03:29.96,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Torakura Ruri (38)\NAsanobu's wife
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.33,0:03:33.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about you, Kishiharu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, then? Want some sake?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.34,0:03:35.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I'll pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.79,0:03:38.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll just head back to my room, lock the door and go to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.13,0:03:43.57,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Torakura Kishiharu (45)\NThird son of the Torakura family
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.67,0:03:43.57,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I've abstained from sake since the incident of Youko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.57,0:03:44.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.84,0:03:47.85,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Hinohara Hikaru (24)\NTorakura Household Maid
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.95,0:03:46.95,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I told you to get the hell out!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.95,0:03:48.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jouhei...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.79,0:03:51.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.48,0:03:52.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.69,0:03:55.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And to think here I was about to comfort you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.22,0:03:57.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the hell's wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.40,0:04:00.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your sister was killed, yet you're not sad about it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.89,0:04:04.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh well, it's not like we have the same mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.83,0:04:07.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's more, she was a formidable love rival.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.20,0:04:13.69,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,So you mean to say the two of us are meant to be together?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.20,0:04:13.69,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Hagawa Jouhei (29)\NKamiyo's lover
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.25,0:04:15.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't mess with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.54,0:04:18.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.49,0:04:20.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.77,0:04:22.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, sake?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.21,0:04:24.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can I have it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.37,0:04:25.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, definitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.08,0:04:29.54,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Torakura Mina (26)\NSecond daughter of the Torakura Family
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.08,0:04:29.54,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,For some reason, I'm really in the mood for drinking tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.94,0:04:39.82,Signs,,0,0,0,,Gunma Prefectural Police
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.63,0:04:38.43,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Ehh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.43,0:04:41.28,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Since then, one more person was killed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.28,0:04:42.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that for real, Hei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.80,0:04:43.75,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.75,0:04:47.35,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A phone was ringing in the middle of the\Nforest so the gatekeepers noticed it andâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.35,0:04:49.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My daughter's safe, isn't she?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.70,0:04:53.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well... she's leisurely making gyoza with Kazuha, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.05,0:04:55.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gyoza?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.10,0:04:58.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then? You haven't figured out who the culprit is, yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.14,0:04:58.81,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.20,0:05:01.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've already figured that out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.23,0:05:02.07,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.63,0:05:05.82,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Nobody can do this trick other than that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.84,0:05:09.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, bind them and handcuff them already! Handcuff them!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.55,0:05:11.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Handcuff...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.15,0:05:13.02,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.27,0:05:17.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't have evidence and there still\Nremains a trick which I haven't solved yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.91,0:05:22.43,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Say, do you believe it's possible for\Nsomeone to slip out of the gate unnoticed,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.43,0:05:27.51,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}strangle someone to death and then slip secretly back inside the gates?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.51,0:05:28.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.70,0:05:31.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Naturally, there are sensors installed over the fences
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.87,0:05:35.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and they are set up so it'll be known\Nimmediately if anyone tries to climb over.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.83,0:05:40.08,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The only time the gatekeepers took their eyes\Noff the gates was when the tunnel collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.08,0:05:40.88,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}How about it?{What do you think?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.68,0:05:48.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, couldn't they have killed Kamiyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Ninside of the fences, tossed her out and run for it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.57,0:05:49.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you an idiot?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.76,0:05:51.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How absurd do you think their strength is?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.24,0:05:56.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Something's on my knee.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.79,0:06:00.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I did go down on one knee while inspecting\NKamiyo{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s body in the forest, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.09,0:06:02.32,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.32,0:06:03.88,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Those white crystals...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.32,0:06:05.99,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}which were mixed in with the mud.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.16,0:06:08.78,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This texture...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.78,0:06:10.89,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Could it be salt?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.89,0:06:13.45,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But why was it in such a place?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.85,0:06:18.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but no matter how much they trained by lifting\Nbarbells in the gym, it'd still be impossible, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.32,0:06:20.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tying a body to a stick andâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.36,0:06:20.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.31,0:06:22.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ba...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.42,0:06:23.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Barbell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.89,0:06:28.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, I've clearly figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.47,0:06:32.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That the opponent isn't a vampire who\Ngrew wings or anything of the sort.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.24,0:06:34.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.64,0:06:36.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're a demon all right...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.80,0:06:39.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But they're more of a bloodthirsty killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.99,0:07:11.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.30,0:07:13.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A text message from the master?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.88,0:07:19.00,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Come to the Southeast Asia room to hear\Nthe important topic you missed this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.00,0:07:22.33,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Naturally, take extra care not to be noticed by anyone and come alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.58,0:07:24.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Torakura Hakuya.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.67,0:07:26.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What could it be about, I wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.89,0:07:30.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be the master's safe and he knows the identity of the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.31,0:07:34.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he certainly looked vampire-ish, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.33,0:07:35.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.08,0:07:41.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We need to talk for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.50,0:07:43.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.36,0:07:51.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Expectedly, I'm starting to feel sleepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.72,0:07:54.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no! It's already five in the morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.14,0:07:56.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have to go to sleep fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.94,0:07:58.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, a phone call.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.06,0:07:59.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's from Heiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.72,0:08:01.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's it, Heiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.08,0:08:02.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You got hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.42,0:08:05.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There're still plenty of gyoza left!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.14,0:08:05.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.38,0:08:10.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah... Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.50,0:08:12.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah... Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.83,0:08:13.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.96,0:08:16.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.86,0:08:19.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, do you have a hairpin on you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.93,0:08:20.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.84,0:08:33.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.02,0:08:35.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.77,0:08:37.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Hikaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.08,0:08:40.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I came here upon receiving your text message.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.52,0:08:42.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master~
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.24,0:08:49.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}With this...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.41,0:08:51.36,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's the end!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.62,0:09:07.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.91,0:09:09.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.58,0:09:11.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't come out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.67,0:09:14.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You only need to support us by voice!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.46,0:09:15.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,G-Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.84,0:09:17.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.46,0:09:19.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They've disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.05,0:09:20.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-They've really...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.93,0:09:23.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.05,0:09:49.06,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.30,0:09:52.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}M-My body's stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.42,0:09:53.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.70,0:09:58.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a passage the master made especially for Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.58,0:10:01.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way it'd fit for your body, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.54,0:10:04.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hagawa Jouhei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.44,0:10:10.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the master has been giving Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} clothes as presents...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.79,0:10:14.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he must've asked Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} about\Nher body size and came to know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.97,0:10:16.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.08,0:10:20.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tragic events that occurred tonight were\Nserial murders entrusted by the master to Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.85,0:10:22.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those tricks in their entirety which the\Nmaster tried to tell to her this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.90,0:10:27.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,by sending her a text message and calling\Nher out to the Southeast Asia room
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.56,0:10:29.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were the one who snatched them away, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.56,0:10:33.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The text message which was sent to Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nphone while it was left charging in the restroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.73,0:10:38.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We are well aware that you looked at it without permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.58,0:10:43.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't notice that\Ntext message until well past noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.62,0:10:45.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Why me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.88,0:10:49.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't Kishiharu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who arrived before\Nnoon also have the chance to look at it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.99,0:10:55.75,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The message said "After breakfast, come\Nto the Southeast Asia room," you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.75,0:11:01.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If one saw such a text message just before noon, they'd\Nthink the master's no longer waiting, wouldn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.01,0:11:03.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if that text message was unread,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.50,0:11:07.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They'd either think the two met somewhere\Nby coincidence and talked over, or...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.57,0:11:13.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They'd at least think the master, who had\Nbeen stood up, gave up and went to sleep.{**Check tenses}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.35,0:11:16.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If someone were to have looked at that text\Nmessage and go to the Southeast Asia room...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.89,0:11:21.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could've only been you or Kamiyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who\Narrived here the previous day and stayed overnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.68,0:11:24.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since Kamiyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.30,0:11:26.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That leaves only you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.88,0:11:30.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's also the possibility that the butler\Nor the maids might've looked at it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.70,0:11:35.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fact that the master addressed such an\Nimportant matter by a text message means...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.59,0:11:42.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was confident that there isn't a rude person who'd read\Nothers' text messages without permission in the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.10,0:11:45.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, having become curious about what it could be...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.18,0:11:49.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You sneaked to the Southeast Asia room and ended up seeing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.66,0:11:53.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The dead sight of the master who cut off his head using the guillotine!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.65,0:11:59.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They must've been left beside his body.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.69,0:12:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The master's phone, the freezer's key, the tunnel's detonating switch...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.41,0:12:08.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As well as the plans for those serial murders!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.21,0:12:11.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Don't spout things as if you saw them happen yourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.20,0:12:17.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, there are plenty of tricks in those\Nserial murders which couldn't be done...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.01,0:12:19.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,unless the master's head was {\i1}severed!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.01,0:12:23.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of which is the trick behind the master's sudden disappearance from inside the coffin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.92,0:12:27.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd have been rather easy if the master did it himself, however...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.62,0:12:33.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was someone else using his body, they wouldn't\Nhave been able to do it unless it was just the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.48,0:12:40.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Despite us rushing over immediately upon hearing the screams\Nof the ladies as they saw the master dead inside the coffin...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.45,0:12:48.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You sneaked to the storage room below it and\Nused the secret passage to retrieve the head, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.35,0:12:52.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, of what Kazuha saw, only the head was real.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.01,0:12:55.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for the body, you stuffed the clothes\Nwith something to shape them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.42,0:13:00.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were the body to be real as well, it'd have swayed and made noises
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.58,0:13:03.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when you pulled it out of the coffin and it'd have been exposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.38,0:13:08.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, using the remote, you released the lock on the coffin's lid.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.91,0:13:11.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And while everyone was taken aback by the master's disappearance,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.37,0:13:17.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You carried the master's head to the closet in the room\Nnext to the one where the picture was taken, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.20,0:13:20.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to have that ghost photography taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.36,0:13:25.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since the closet had a bar for hanging hangers to begin with,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.49,0:13:27.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,hanging the master's head was easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.86,0:13:29.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you did a such thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.59,0:13:32.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you arrived to the room with the coffin\Na little late than everyone, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.96,0:13:35.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That ghost photography...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.67,0:13:38.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was you, who were beside the one-way mirror, who did it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.07,0:13:44.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd be able to use your own body position to prevent\NKamiyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was beside you, from blocking the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.60,0:13:50.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, if you had the remote for the light used\Nto light up the master's face inside of the closet...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.75,0:13:53.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then by pressing it at the right time,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.02,0:13:57.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd be able to make the master's face emerge inside of the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.49,0:14:04.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, the last trick was making the master\Nappear upside-down at the dining room's window.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.31,0:14:07.01,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A strange shadow, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.00,0:14:15.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You waited at the smoking room for Asanobu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to come...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.06,0:14:20.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after you seized a chance and killed\Nhim by slicing open his carotid artery...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.04,0:14:24.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You passed a fishing line through the hinges\Nof the shutters in the smoking room...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.90,0:14:28.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then you made both ends hang next to the window of the dining room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.21,0:14:31.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You attached the master's head on one end...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.17,0:14:35.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And hooked the other end to the window frame of the dining room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.06,0:14:39.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So once the window had been opened, the thread\Nwould be released and the head will fall down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.03,0:14:41.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Wait a sec!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.65,0:14:45.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't he disappear upwards when I opened the window?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.14,0:14:52.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that was just the head, then couldn't\Nsomeone have been up there and pulled it up?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.74,0:14:53.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A convex lens.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.04,0:15:00.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The upper right pane of that window alone became\Na convex lens just like a magnifying glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.54,0:15:04.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Through that lens, things appear inverted at a certain viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.42,0:15:09.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why even though it fell downwards, it appeared as if it went upwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.17,0:15:14.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, the three panes below the convex lens are ordinary glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.28,0:15:18.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Naturally, if the head were to be seen\Nas it fell down, the trick won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.43,0:15:23.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why this trick couldn't have\Nbeen done by anyone other than you,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.18,0:15:26.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who blocked the view of the lower three\Npanes with your own body at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.12,0:15:33.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where the head fell into was an urn left in advance in the\Nveranda outside that window, along with the flowerpots.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.64,0:15:39.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we went to check afterwards, only that urn was\Nset aside and the master's head was still inside of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.43,0:15:48.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, had Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} not told us "The master's shadow which\Nwas lit up by lightning appeared from below on the curtains,"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.70,0:15:50.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we wouldn't have noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.58,0:15:54.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right after that, The huge bird we saw was...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.74,0:15:56.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a wing-flapping airplane.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.41,0:16:04.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you left it on the roof outside of the smoking room and\Nstarted its motor by a remote just before opening the window...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.30,0:16:10.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd fly away in the sky just as you open\Nthe window and that was your setup.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.44,0:16:14.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, the airplane is bound to be found later somewhere in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.28,0:16:18.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In-In that case, what about the one who killed honey in the forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.41,0:16:20.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying I'm the one who did that as well?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.92,0:16:25.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The gatekeepers only looked aside for a single\Nmoment, and honey was tied to a stick, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.07,0:16:29.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For me, who never left the mansion, doing such a thing is justâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.00,0:16:31.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ice wheels!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.76,0:16:39.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You attached ice wheels to the stick, which the\Nstrangled Kamiyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was tied to, just like a barbell!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.93,0:16:44.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you blew up the tunnel and in the instant\Nthe gatekeepers were distracted by it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.62,0:16:48.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you'd rolled it from the top of the stairs in front of the gate...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.12,0:16:52.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The body will, while suffering injuries\Nto its fingertips, pass through the gate,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.45,0:16:55.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,bump into a tree and stop in the middle of the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.35,0:16:59.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you just had to estimate the time necessary for the ice to melt...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.35,0:17:04.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and ring Kamiyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s phone to make the gatekeepers discover it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.52,0:17:08.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tonight's hot and humid, and what's more rain had been falling down.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.44,0:17:13.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since it seems the ice was made with salt mixed in, it melted easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.79,0:17:18.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Incidentally, the ice wheels were made by the key-locked freezer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.38,0:17:22.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You put up the seaweed can in the\Nmiddle of the pool intended for kids...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.44,0:17:27.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and in order to make two wheels, you divided\Nit up at the halfway mark by a paper or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.66,0:17:34.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since you took out those wheels from the\Nfreezer and rolled them all the way until the stairs...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.11,0:17:39.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of the flour the ladies spilled on the flour, only\Nthe portion about the width of the wheels came off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.98,0:17:44.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez. Even though these brats have no\Nevidence, they dare say whatever they like!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.42,0:17:46.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for evidence, you have it on you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.97,0:17:52.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason why you didn't delete the master's\Ntext message from Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.18,0:17:54.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was to pin all of the crimes on her, afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.80,0:17:56.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.93,0:18:01.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why we thought you'd call Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} somewhere to silence her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.95,0:18:09.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because you had this murder plan which was\Nmade for Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} by the master on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.65,0:18:15.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the evidence, Hagawa Jouhei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.77,0:18:24.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it says on this plan, "Call Hagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to the Southeast Asia\Nroom, kill him, lock the door, and get out through this passage,"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.30,0:18:28.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wanted to make it seem as if Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Ncalled you out, according to the plan...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.81,0:18:34.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And as she attacked you, you killed her in self-defense, is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.46,0:18:39.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, if you left the plan beside\NHikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body and called everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.94,0:18:46.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your plan of the bloodthirsty killer being killed by their\Nown victim while on spree would be completed, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.56,0:18:47.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.02,0:18:50.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could such brats figure it out...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.06,0:18:52.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't supposed to come to light!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.86,0:19:00.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was when you said to examine the blood found inside the coffin\Nmore throughly that I had my eye on you and began to suspect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.45,0:19:01.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.92,0:19:05.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was just blood that dripped\Nwhen I put the head inside the coffin.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.40,0:19:09.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That blood was determined as a different blood type\Nfrom the person's blood type itself, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.89,0:19:11.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was obviously an error made by the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.99,0:19:16.51,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The blood spot we found at the coffin\Nback then, was it really of type AB?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.58,0:19:22.08,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Actually, shouldn't we have that blood examined more in depth?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.08,0:19:23.47,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Like checking the DNA.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.93,0:19:26.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The master probably had cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.66,0:19:30.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At its terminal stage, it is also possible for the blood type to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.58,0:19:33.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's type A, it becomes type AB.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.48,0:19:35.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if it's type O, it becomes type B.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.62,0:19:38.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For one to be able to say it was a lab test error from the very beginning...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.90,0:19:43.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,they can only be the culprit, who actually\Nplaced the master's head inside the coffin.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.69,0:19:47.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it seems that your blood, due to following this plan...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.43,0:19:53.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,has pitifully changed into the blood of a brutal bloodthirsty killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.95,0:21:21.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My dear daughter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.46,0:21:25.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The beginning of that plan opened with "my dear daughter"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.74,0:21:26.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.79,0:21:30.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To keep the mansion's fine butler from figuring it\Nout, it seems that the master has lied to him, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.35,0:21:36.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the will and the DNA test found in the\Nmaster's room, there's no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.11,0:21:41.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he really tried to make his daughter commit serial murders?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.74,0:21:42.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.93,0:21:49.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He deliberately put on fake fangs to make everyone believe\Nthe crimes were his doing after having turned into a vampire...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.26,0:21:55.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The motive was revenge to Youko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who was ought to be his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.24,0:21:59.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently, Hagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was arrested, has spilled the beans.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.19,0:22:06.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Youko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s accidental death was plotted by the maid\NShimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Kamiyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Asanobu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.42,0:22:10.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, as we thought, the incident\Nof Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from half a year ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.34,0:22:13.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...must be the deed of the master.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.36,0:22:17.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While the will said that he sucked the blood himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.75,0:22:23.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the master was a doctor so he must have made\Nher take a drug which works as a blood thinner,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.07,0:22:26.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then he inserted a catheter in her artery and drew the blood out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.52,0:22:31.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, the reason he tied Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nto a stick and put it upside-down...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.81,0:22:35.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was to make the ice wheels trick harder to figure out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.83,0:22:40.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, had Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} been the first to see the plans...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.67,0:22:42.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would've been alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.02,0:22:42.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.03,0:22:45.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was written at the end of the plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.78,0:22:48.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"However, if you're to forgive everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.63,0:22:48.84,Signs,,0,0,0,,Torakura Hakuya
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.80,0:22:52.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then along with the revenge flames invested in my body,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.39,0:22:54.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,dispose of this letter."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.78,0:22:58.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believe Hikaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would've surely chosen the latter.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.51,0:23:00.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.73,0:23:04.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, that Hagawa guy is really an outrageous bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.78,0:23:07.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think he anticipated he'd be able to go back with Mina{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.01,0:23:12.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He put his lover to death according to plan,\Nand still tried to seize the money...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.50,0:23:16.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, there is no denying he was a foolish man.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.70,0:23:20.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should take good care as much as possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.80,0:23:23.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Women are scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.02,0:23:24.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.16,0:23:25.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.74,0:23:33.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, w-wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.19,0:23:40.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This smell...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.96,0:23:42.98,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Just how many gyoza did you eat?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:24:08.92,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.36,0:23:49.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To tell the truth, this letter was delivered to my place.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.44,0:23:53.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Izumi Jisaborou-shi's life is being targeted.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.53,0:23:54.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.68,0:24:00.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't let my guard down in front of any of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.91,0:24:05.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, let's trust the little boy who saved me.
